      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 869: `handlePendingConversation()` clears the tombstone whenever `reinvitePending` is true, but it does not verify that the pending clone being finalized is the clone started by accepting the stored re-invitation. If another pending/bootstrap clone for the same removed conversation completes after `reinvitePending` is armed, it can resurrect the conversation and remove the request even though the accepted re-invite clone has not succeeded. Tie the marker to the accepted request/clone attempt, for example by storing the expected inviter/device or a clone attempt id in `PendingConversationFetch` and checking it before clearing `removed`/`erased`.\n```suggestion\n            if (conv-\u003ereinvitePending \u0026\u0026 conv-\u003epending \u0026\u0026 conv-\u003epending-\u003eisReinviteClone) {\n                conv-\u003einfo.created \u003d std::time(nullptr);\n                conv-\u003einfo.removed \u003d 0;\n                conv-\u003einfo.erased \u003d 0;\n                addConvInfo(conv-\u003einfo);\n                reinviteAccepted \u003d true;\n            } else {\n                removeRepo \u003d true;\n            }\n```",
