      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agreed this is a hardening opportunity rather than a correctness bug in the current flow. The window is bounded in practice: there is a single `conv-\u003epending` slot, `startFetch()` rejects a concurrent fetch for the same conversation (\"Already fetching\", line 1389), and every local removal resets `reinvitePending` and bumps `removalGeneration` under `conv-\u003emtx`. So the only clone that can observe `reinvitePending \u003d\u003d true` is the one armed by the accepted re-invitation.\n\nThat said, tying the marker to the specific clone attempt (e.g. an `isReinviteClone` flag carried in `PendingConversationFetch`, checked before clearing removed/erased) would make the invariant explicit and future-proof. Happy to add that if you prefer — leaving this open for Adrien / François-Simon to weigh in.",
