      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is already guarded. `cloneConversationFrom(const ConversationRequest\u0026, std::optional\u003cuint64_t\u003e)` takes `std::lock_guard lk(conv-\u003emtx);` at the top of the function (line 1514, pre-existing context), and that lock covers the whole `else if (conv-\u003einfo.isRemoved())` branch: the `isRemoved()` test, the `expectedRemovalGeneration !\u003d conv-\u003eremovalGeneration` comparison, the members/mode refresh, and the `reinvitePending \u003d true` write. So the re-invitation state is read and mutated under `conv-\u003emtx` — the same mutex every removal path uses.\n\nThe generation check is exactly what closes the accept→clone window: `acceptConversationRequest()` snapshots `removalGeneration` under `conv-\u003emtx`, and this branch re-validates it under `conv-\u003emtx` before arming the marker, so a concurrent local removal is detected and the clone aborted, not missed.\n\nAlso note `SyncedConversation::mtx` is a non-recursive `std::mutex` (line 58): the suggested edit would take a second `std::lock_guard` on the already-held mutex in the same call stack and deadlock. Marking resolved as a false positive.",
